</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="names">
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Names.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Myanmar</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">boktaung</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">wetkyein</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">maha-gar-kyan-sit.</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">English</emphasis>
: Chinese knotweed, Chinese smartweed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">North temperate. Found in China, Bhutan, India, Indonesia, Japan, Malaysia, Myanmar, Nepal, Philippines, Sikkim, Thailand, and Vietnam. In Myanmar found in Ayeyarwady, Bago, Kachin, Mandalay, and Yangon.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="143" type="use">
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Use.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Whole plant</emphasis>
: Used as an antiscorbutic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
